<p>At least 55 people have died across six provinces in south-central Vietnam after a week of flooding, and rescuers are searching for 13 missing, authorities said Saturday [dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#1][firstpost.com#1]. Heavy rains since late October inundated Nha Trang and triggered landslides near Da Lat; further heavy rain is forecast in coming days [dawn.com#1][thehindu.com#1][abc.net.au#1]. Multiple highways remain impassable and about 300,000 people are still without power—down from an initial outage affecting more than a million [dawn.com#1][firstpost.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/NxpBVhAEPmMb6LHOP-dr_oJeX4-GE_v1NQles5W0vdhp4T_4uchTgTMtH5Talu-HCfcZEBdl71PzA6u3JLcp6CpTbgN_QK4a0-AbWr0Drr8P' alt='People walk past debris after floods in central Vietnam, November 1, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Hardest hit: Mountainous Dak Lak province recorded more than two dozen fatalities, the most among affected regions [dawn.com#1]</li><li>Rainfall totals: Some locations have received more than 1.5 metres of rain, with further heavy rainfall expected [abc.net.au#1]</li><li>Infrastructure strain: Several highways remain blocked and roughly 300,000 people are still without electricity after an earlier outage affected over a million [dawn.com#1][firstpost.com#1]</li><li>Active rescues: Teams have been retrieving people from treetops and rooftops as waters recede in parts of the region [dawn.com#1]</li><li>Climate context: Scientists have identified a pattern of human-driven climate change making extreme weather more frequent and destructive [dawn.com#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Vietnam’s environment ministry: Reported at least 55 deaths, 13 missing, widespread power outages, and impassable highways following days of flooding [dawn.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956688/vietnam-flooding-death-toll-rises-to-55-as-rescuers-race-to-find-more-than-a-dozen-missing'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Rescue services: Teams are racing to locate the missing and have been rescuing people from treetops and roofs as waters recede [dawn.com#1][firstpost.com#1]. (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956688/vietnam-flooding-death-toll-rises-to-55-as-rescuers-race-to-find-more-than-a-dozen-missing'>Dawn; Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Meteorological authorities: Warn of continued heavy rains and further flooding risk in central provinces [abc.net.au#1]. (<a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-11-22/vietnam-floods-death-toll-rises-to-41-more-rain-forecast/106040388'>ABC News (Australia)</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1956688/vietnam-flooding-death-toll-rises-to-55-as-rescuers-race-to-find-more-than-a-dozen-missing'>Vietnam flooding death toll rises to 55 as rescuers race to find more than a dozen missing</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/several-killed-central-vietnam-floods-updates/article70310368.ece'>Vietnam flooding death toll rises to 55</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.abc.net.au/news/2025-11-22/vietnam-floods-death-toll-rises-to-41-more-rain-forecast/106040388'>Death toll rises to 41 in central Vietnam flooding, more heavy rain forecast</a> - abc.net.au</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/vietnam-flood-rescuers-race-to-find-missing-as-death-toll-rises-to-55-13953006.html'>Vietnam flood: Rescuers race to find missing as death toll rises to 55</a> - firstpost.com</li></ul>